<i> to experience withdrawal
 and want higher,</i>

00:03:20.099 --> 00:03:21.901
<i> more dangerous doses--
 which means we were lied to</i>

00:03:21.934 --> 00:03:23.636
<i> by kindly
 CD-hat doctor-type guy.</i>

00:03:23.669 --> 00:03:26.706 line:0%
They do not have
serious medical side effects.

00:03:26.739 --> 00:03:28.507
<i> What the (bleep), dude?
 They hid the evidence</i>

00:03:28.540 --> 00:03:30.643
<i> of illegal Oxy rings,
 and in 2007,</i>

00:03:30.676 --> 00:03:32.812
<i> they lost
 a $635 million lawsuit</i>

00:03:32.845 --> 00:03:35.648
<i> and three executives pleaded
 guilty in misbranding the drug</i>

00:03:35.681 --> 00:03:37.183
<i> and downplaying
 the risk of addiction.</i>

00:03:37.216 --> 00:03:39.619
<i> Even Big Tobacco was like,
 "Damn, you guys are scumbags."</i>

00:03:39.652 --> 00:03:41.220
<i> That lawsuit
 was known years ago,</i>

00:03:41.253 --> 00:03:43.322
<i> but we're only addressing
 this crisis now. Why?</i>

00:03:43.355 --> 00:03:46.025
For the first time
in any first-world country,

00:03:46.058 --> 00:03:47.293
the death rate for white,

00:03:47.326 --> 00:03:49.562
middle-aged people
is on the rise.

00:03:49.595 --> 00:03:51.364
<i> Yep, opioids became
 a national epidemic</i>

